<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3 kg of Heroin Seized at Karachi Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Customs Drug
Enforcement (CDE) staff posted at Karachi International Airport
Friday nabbed a Pakistani passenger and recovered three kilogram
heroin from him, according to the Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The man was leaving for Dhaka by Emirate Airline flight EK-610
when he was apprehended by the CDE staff.
</P>
<P>
An examination of his baggage resulted in the recovery of the
drug of brown color heroin powder concealed in 325 toffees of
different brands and in the false bottom of his hand bag. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
