<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment in Switzerland Down to Years' Lowest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland saw its unemployment
dropping to 1.8 percent in June from 1.9 percent in May, the
lowest since the middle of the 1990s, local press reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss Radio International quoted the latest available data
as saying that the country's jobless people totaled some 66,000 in
June, 3,900 fewer than in May. Meanwhile, the number of people
registered as job-seekers declined by 5,000 to 120,000.
</P>
<P>
At present, only five cantons of the country's 26 total have a
jobless rate above two percent, which are Geneva, Vaud, Ticino,
Neuchatel and Basel-City.
</P>
<P>
It added that Geneva remains the one suffering the worst
situation with the unemployment rate at 4.3 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
