<HEADLINE> Iraq Beats Nepal in Asian Youth U-19 Football Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Favorite Iraq made a cracking start
Friday, crushing Nepal by seven goals as the qualifying round of
32nd Asian Youth Under-19 Football Championship kicked off in
Rajshahi, a northeastern city of Bangladesh, the United News of
Bangladesh reported.
</P>
<P>
Asian soccer giant Iraqis totally shaped the match into a one-
sided encounter, forcing the Himalayan Kingdom of Nepal into a
helpless drift in the inaugural match.
</P>
<P>
The Gulf team most of the time possessed the ball and launched
blitzs one after another, overrunning the opposition fort.
</P>
</TEXT>
