<HEADLINE> Fujian Destroys Counterfeit Foreign Cigarettes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 7 (Xinhua) -- A total of 18,000 cartons of
counterfeit foreign cigarettes were destroyed today in east China'
s Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
The fake cigarettes, including counterfeits of Marlboro, the
brand name of Philip Morris, were seized when they were being
smuggled outside China, according to the customs officials.
</P>
<P>
The customs has launched an investigation in a bid to tackle
smuggling and counterfeiting rings in Fujian's Yunxiao County.
</P>
</TEXT>
