<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OAU Panel Urges to Prevent Rwanda-like Genocide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOME, July 7 (Xinhua) -- A panel formed by the Organization of
African Unity (OAU) Friday called on the international community
to take serious measures to prevent the repeat of the 1994
genocide in Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
The call was made by former Botswanan president Ketumile
Masire, who chaired the OAU panel investigating the 1994 Rwanda
genocide, when he presented a report to the OAU Secretary-General
on his investigation.
</P>
<P>
In the report entitled "Rwanda, The Preventable Genocide", the
panel accused the United Nations Security Council, influenced by
the United States, France and Belgium, of failing to prevent the
genocide from taking place.
</P>
<P>
It urged all those parties that have apologized for their role
in the genocide and those who have yet to apologize to support the
Secretary- General of the United Nations to establish a commission
to set a formula for reparations for the genocide victims and to
identify which countries have an obligation to pay them.
</P>
<P>
"The funds paid as reparations should be devoted to urgently
needed infrastructure developments and social service improvements
on behalf of all Rwandans," it said.
</P>
<P>
The panel also urged the present government of Rwanda to
acknowledge that it is unrealistic to pretend that ethnicity is no
longer a political factor in the country.
</P>
<P>
"We urge all Rwandans, both in government and civil society, to
work together to forge a untied society based on the inherent
strength and rich heritage of Rwanda's diverse ethnic
communities," the panel said in its recommendations.
</P>
<P>
It also called on all countries either to extradite accused
genocide leaders they are harboring or to try them in exile to
bring all leaders of the genocide to trial with the utmost speed.
</P>
<P>
The International Panel of Eminent Personalities to Investigate
the 1994 Genocide in Rwanda and the Surrounding Events was created
in 1998 by OAU with a mandate to investigate the 1994 genocide in
Rwanda and the surrounding events in the Great Lakes Region as
part of the efforts aimed at averting and preventing further
wide-scale conflicts in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000708.0012 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, Saturday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD-- The first locally-constructed oil refinery in Iraq,
with a capacity of 10,000 barrels a day, is expected to go into
operation in the next few days, the official Iraqi News Agency
(INA) reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Citing an official at the Ministry of Industry and Minerals, the
INA said the oil refinery is located in Baiji area, some 200
kilometers north of the capital Baghdad.
</P>
<P>
The success of building small oil refineries will encourage Iraq
to build big ones to break foreign monopoly in this field, said the
official. (BC-Iraq-Oil Refinery)
</P>
<P>
EHRAN -- Iranian students started the day quietly on Saturday,
holding no rallies or demonstrations to mark the first anniversary
of the Tehran University student dormitory incident that sparked
widespread riots last July.
</P>
<P>
On the streets and city squares of Tehran, the stream of cars
flow as usual, and people walk their way or wait for their buses
quietly. No student gatherings are in sight. Even the Tehran
University is in a tranquil atmosphere, with not many students in
the campus.
</P>
<P>
On July 8 last year, Tehran was the battleground of the heaviest
clashes between the security forces and protesting students after
the culmination of the 1979 Islamic revolution.(BC-Iran-Dormitory
Incident)
</P>
<P>
TEHRNA -- Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman Hamid Reza Asefi
has strongly lashed out at the United States for its stance against
Iran's verdicts on 10 Iranian Jews on charge of spying for Israel.
</P>
<P>
"The government of the Islamic Republic of Iran does not allow
any foreign country to interfere in Iran's internal affairs," Asefi
said on Friday evening, quoted by the Islamic Republic News Agency
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He said the Iranian judiciary is entitled to deal independently
with judicial matters in the country.
</P>
<P>
"How can American officials allow themselves to interfere with
such impudence in the internal affairs of the Islamic Republic of
Iran?" he questioned.(BC-Iran-U.S.-Jews)
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- The Palestinian delegation to the upcoming U.S.-Israeli-
Palestinian summit at Camp David next Tuesday will also include
representatives from three opposition factions in the Palestine
Liberation Organization (PLO), said a PLO official Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from the Democratic Front for the Liberation of
Palestine, the Palestinian People's Party (the former Communist
Party) and the Popular Struggle Front will join the Palestinian
delegation to the summit, said Taysir Khaled, a member of the PLO
executive committee.
</P>
<P>
"The political delegation to the summit was formed on Friday
during the executive committee meeting," said Khaled from the
Democratic Front.(BC-Palestine-Opposition-Summit) 
</P>
</TEXT>
