<HEADLINE> OPEC Experts Open Preparatory Meeting for September Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The experts from 11 member states of
the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) gathered
here Saturday for a preparatory meeting for the OPEC summit in
Caracas, capital of Venezuela, in September.
</P>
<P>
Algerian Minister of Energy and Mines Chakib Khelil and his
Venezuelan counterpart Ali Rodriguez, currently OPEC president, and
OPEC Secretary-General Alhaji Rilwanu Lukman attended the inaugural
session of the meeting, the Algerian News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day meeting, experts are to prepare a set of
documents, recommendations, proposals, programs, memos and
communique for the September summit.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, the experts will mull over the future role of
the cartel in the global economy, environmental protection and the
development of appropriate technology.
</P>
<P>
They are also expected to discuss the issue of boosting and
beefing up technological cooperation between OPEC member states and
non-OPEC producers and consumers.
</P>
<P>
The OPEC members are Algeria, Indonesia, Iran, Iraq, Kuwait,
Libya, Nigeria, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates and
Venezuela. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
