<DOCNO> XIE20000708.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OPEC Chief to Visit UAE on Tour of Oil Producers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan Minister of Energy and
Mines Ali Rodriguez, currently president of the Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC), will visit the United Arab
Emirates (UAE) next Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He will hold talks with UAE Minister of Petroleum and Mineral
Resources Obeid bin Saif Al Nasir on the latest developments on the
world oil market, the official WAM news agency reported Saturday.
The OPEC chief, to be accompanied by a high-ranking delegation,
will also discuss with UAE officials on arrangements for the OPEC
summit to be held in Caracas, capital of Venezuela, in September.
</P>
<P>
Rodriguez's visit to the Emirates will be part of his week-long
tour of OPEC member states. It will also prepare for an official
visit to UAE by Venezuelan President Hugo Rafael Chavez Frias in
August.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, President Chavez will invite UAE President
Zayed bin Sultan Al-Nahyan to attend the OPEC summit. 
</P>
