<HEADLINE> Chile's Foreign Debt Near 35 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Chile's foreign debt grew 982
million dollars during the first five months of this year up to 34.
991 billion dollars at the close of May 31, as reported Saturday
by the Central Bank of this country.
</P>
<P>
Most of it, 83.4 percent, or 29.213 billion dollars, is owed by
the private sector, and only 16.6 percent, or 5.778 billion
dollars, is a public sector liability.
</P>
<P>
Chilean Central Bank statistics show that the medium and long
term foreign debt during that period was 30.658 billion dollars,
because the public debt amounted to 4.74 billion dollars, while
the private debt was 25.918 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The short term foreign debt was up to May 31 of this year 4.333
billion dollars, where the credits contracted for up to one year
maturity amounted to 1.01 billion dollars and the amortization of
medium and long term credits up to 12 months were a total of 3.323
billion dollars.  
</P>
