<HEADLINE> Egypt Sends Pharaonic Treasures to Japan for Exhibitions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Over 120 pieces of antiquities dating back to various eras of
ancient Egypt will go on display in the National Tokyo Museum for
two months before touring the country, the first ever of its kind,
said Akira Takazawa of Japan's NHK public television which is
sponsoring the event.
</P>
