<HEADLINE> AOL Sites Rank First in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After AOL, Microsoft sites ranked second, with 49.3 million
visitors, and Yahoo sites ranked third, with 48.9 million, in
Media Metrix's U.S. Top 50 Web and Digital Media Properties.
</P>
<P>
The study showed that Internet users spent an average of 177.8
minutes surfing news, information and entertainment sites in May,
up 35.6 percent from January. The study found people spent an
average 182.6 minutes surfing these sites at work and 128.6
minutes at home.
</P>
<P>
Media Metrix also tracked May's top 25 advertisers and ranked
each product segment by ad impressions, the number of times an ad
is rendered for viewing. Capital One was the top Internet
advertiser, with 1.2 billion ads.
</P>
<P>
In terms of product segments, Visa-affiliated credit cards were
the biggest online advertisers with 1.6 billion ads, followed by
portal and search engines with 1.1 billion and online communities,
and chat sites with one billion. 
</P>
