<HEADLINE> Russian Pakhalina Regains European Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Yulia Pakhalina of Russia has come
back to her prodigious best to reclaim her European three-meter
springboard diving crown with a colossal win in the final on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The world champion, who missed last year's championships for
testing positive for caffeine, amassed 578.37 points from her five
semi-final and five final dives, nearly 50 points clear of her
closest rival.
</P>
<P>
Pakhalina won her first European gold in Seville in 1997 after
taking the silver in Vienna in 1995. But she received two-month
ban for failing drug test and was pulled out of the Russian team
for the 1999 European championships.
</P>
<P>
Doerte Lindner of Germany scored an aggregate 528.72 to finish
runner-up and Anna Lindberg of Sweden, bronze medallist in 1997,
took another bronze with 523.77 points.
</P>
<P>
Ilyina, who won the European one-meter springboard title for
the fourth successive time on Tuesday, botched her penultimate
dive and had to settle for fourth place with 500.55 points.
</P>
</TEXT>
