<HEADLINE> Dekker Wins Eighth Stage of Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Dutchman Erik Dekker beat his rivals
to win Saturday's eighth stage of the Tour de France cycle race.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Lance Armstrong remained in the chasing pack
more than six minutes behind, along with his main challengers for
the title, and still looks well-placed before the mountain stages
which begin on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Dekker won the 203-kilometer run from Limoges to Villeneuve-sur-
Lot in southwest France with a time of four hours 22 minutes 14
seconds.
</P>
<P>
Xavier Jan of France finished second with 52 seconds behind and
Jose-Vicente Garcia-Acosta of Spain came in third, 56 seconds
behind the winner. 
</P>
