<HEADLINE> Ningxia Tourism Festival Highlights Desert, Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- An international tourism festival
focusing on adventures in the desert and on China's second-longest
river, the Yellow River, opened today in this capital of northwest
China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Various programs such as rafting along the Yellow River,
traveling in the desert and discovering the folklore of the local
Muslim residents will be presented during the five-day event.
</P>
<P>
Major scenic spots in Ningxia are expected to receive more than
50,000 domestic and overseas visitors during the festival. A trade
fair is being held simultaneously, highlighting package tour
programs, tourist souvenirs and local products.
</P>
<P>
The festival has been jointly organized by the National Tourism
Administration and the Ningxia regional government. 
