<HEADLINE> Nigeria Shifts New League Season for Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The kick-off date for the new season
of the Nigerian league has been shifted from August to October
because of the Sydney Olympics, an official announced here
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 2000/2001 season was delayed as a result of the fact the
country's top soccer officials will all be in Australia for the
Olympics, said the head of the Nigerian league Al-Hassan Yakmut.
</P>
<P>
"All these officials will have to be present for the Annual
General Meeting of the Nigeria Football Association (NFA) before a
kick-off date would be adopted. The new season will now begin in
October," he said. 
</P>
