<HEADLINE> Ministry to Inspect Transport Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) --The Ministry of Communications has
decided to launch a nationwide safety inspection of buses,
passenger ships, dangerous goods ships and warehouses, docks,
stations and water recreation facilities.
</P>
<P>
In an urgent notice issued today to all transport departments,
the ministry said it will send four special groups on July 11 to
inspect boat safety on the Yangtze River, the Qiongzhou Strait,
the Bohai Bay and the Zhoushan Islands.
</P>
<P>
It also ordered the transport departments of all provinces,
autonomous regions and municipalities to launch their own safety
inspections.
</P>
<P>
Leading officials of transport departments should take charge
of the inspections, and vehicles and facilities that fall short of
the safety standards must be put out of operation, it said.
</P>
<P>
The notice was issued in the aftermath of a recent safety-
improvement order from the State Council which followed a series
of alarming traffic accidents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
