<HEADLINE> More Quakes Jolt Bengkulu, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The agency quoted the local geophysics station as saying that
the first earthquake measuring 4.9 on the Richter Scale occurred
at 01:55 a.m. local time (17:55 GMT Friday). The quake centered at
5.75 degrees southern latitude and 101.4 degrees eastern longitude.
</P>
<P>
The second quake measuring 5.1 on the Richter Scale occurred at
11:53 a.m. local time and centered at 5.76 degrees southern
latitude and 101.09 degrees eastern longitude. Seven minutes later,
a quake measuring 4.7 on the Richter Scale jolted Bengkulu again.
The quake centered at 5.79 degrees southern latitude and 101.2
degrees eastern longitude.
</P>
<P>
An earthquake measuring 7.3 on the Richter Scale hit Bengkulu
on June 4. At least 130 people were killed and hundreds of others
injured in the quake which also devastated thousands of buildings.
</P>
<P>
Since the June 4 quake, the local geophysics station has
recorded more than 2,000 aftershocks at different intensities.
</P>
