<HEADLINE> Russia Slams U.S. ABM Test As Challenges to Human Progress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A top Russian military official
Saturday sharply condemned the anti-ballistic missile (ABM) test
conducted by the U.S. Friday night, describing it as "a challenge
to all of progressive mankind."
</P>
<P>
"Although the tests targeted at creating a U.S. national
missile defense system failed, it was a challenge to the world
public," Gen. Vladimir Yakovlev, Chief Commander of the Russian
Strategic Missile Troops, told the press here, after the Pentagon
confirmed the failure of its third missile interruption test early
in the day.
</P>
<P>
"The consequences of the Pentagon's future actions could be
unpredictable," Yakovlev said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, he stressed that Russia's strategic missile
forces are kept at top-level combat readiness, and missile troops
are prepared to fulfill any task set by the supreme command.
