<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Landslides Leave Eight Dead, Thousands Homeless </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Landslides have left eight people
dead, four missing, and over 10,000 homeless in mountainous
Yunyang County, in southwest China's Chongqing City.
</P>
<P>
Yunyang, located in the Three Gorges area of the Yangtze River,
has been hit by a succession of torrential rains, which dumped 354
mm of rain on the area from July 1 to 6, or about one third of the
average annual rainfall.
</P>
<P>
The rains have resulted in large-scale landslides in the county.
In the village of Xinyang, a landslide measuring about two sq km
destroyed 106 houses, leaving some 400 people homeless.
</P>
<P>
So far this summer, eight large-scale landslides and over 1,600
small ones have been recorded in the county, a key area of
relocation for the Three Gorges Project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
