<HEADLINE> India Test Fires Surface-to-Air Missile Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- India's home-developed multi-
target surface-to-air missile Akash Saturday was test fired for
the second time within this week in the eastern coastal state of
Orissa, the Press Trust of India (PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
The missile was fired from a missile launcher at around 11:30 a.
m. on Saturday from the Interim Test Range at Chandipur-on-sea,
the PTI said.
</P>
<P>
The last test firing of Akash occurred only three days ago on
July 5.
</P>
<P>
Saturday's test firing was carried out without any warhead, the
PTI quoted sources at the test range as saying.
</P>
<P>
With a range of 25 km, Akash has a capacity to deliver 55 kg of
both conventional and nuclear explosives, and is also capable of
striking several targets simultaneously. 
</P>
</TEXT>
