<HEADLINE> Iranian Students Mark Dorm-Attack Incident Quietly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Iranian students started the day
quietly on Saturday, holding no rallies or demonstrations to mark
the first anniversary of the Tehran University student dormitory
incident that sparked widespread riots last July.
</P>
<P>
On the streets and city squares of Tehran, the stream of cars
flow as usual, and people walk their way or wait for their buses
quietly. No student gatherings are in sight. Even the Tehran
University is in a tranquil atmosphere, with not many students in
the campus.
</P>
<P>
On July 8 last year, Tehran was the battleground of the heaviest
clashes between the security forces and protesting students after
the culmination of the 1979 Islamic revolution.
</P>
<P>
The Tehran University students, in protest to the closure of an
outspoken daily by the conservative authorities, had staged a rally
on the premises of their dormitory but were raided by the police
and a number of plainclothes men.
</P>
<P>
In the heavy clash, one student died and hundreds were injured.
The incident sparked nation-wide unrest in the next five days.
</P>
<P>
Tehran University students have said that they would mark the
anniversary peacefully and avoid violence and they seem to be
keeping their word.
</P>
<P>
A leading student organization, however, issued a statement
Friday night to mark the occasion, the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, the Office to Foster Unity called on the
Majlis (parliament) to defend people's rights by approving the
required laws for institutionalization of democracy and realization
of the civil society.
</P>
<P>
It urged the Majlis to approve a motion filed by a number of
parliament members last month, which aims to bar police and
military forces from entering universities and research agencies.
</P>
<P>
On the trial of some 20 police officers believed to be involved
in the attack, the statement said that the trial was not enough,
for those who were behind the scene and really responsible for the
incident are still at large.
</P>
<P>
It also called on the students to exercise self-restraint and
steadfastness in facing various kinds of instigation, for any
impulsive or radical behavior may be used by the conservative
establishment to crackdown on the country's reformist movement.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
