<HEADLINE> Kenya Requires Relief Food up to December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Kenya will require relief food up
to December this year as the famine situation is desperate, the
country's Disaster Emergency Response Committee has said.
</P>
<P>
Uhuru Kenyatta, chairman of the committee, appealed here on
Friday to all Kenyans to be at the forefront to the calamity
brought about by rain failure, the Daily Nation newspaper reported
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Kenyatta's appeal came hot on the heels of the World Food
Program warning that Kenya had only one month's stock of relief
food left.
</P>
<P>
David Fletcher, WFP country representative in Nairobi, said on
Wednesday that there would be no food after August to feed
millions of Kenyans affected by famine in 19 districts.
</P>
<P>
According to Kenyatta, the Italian government had responded to
Kenya's appeal by shipping 2,437 tons of food including wheat and
rice which will be distributed to the needy next week.
</P>
<P>
He said between July last year and June this year, the Kenyan
government has bought 438,217 bags of maize (90 kilograms per
bag) for distribution to famine victims. 
</P>
</TEXT>
