<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A trade union to look into the
interests of all technical and professional employees in the field
of agriculture has been formed in Zambia, the Zambia Daily Mail
newspaper reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The union, which is called Agriculture Technical and
Professional Staff Union, will look forward to negotiating with
the government and other stakeholders to improve the salaries and
conditions of service for all agriculture technical and
professional staff, said the union's interim president Sam Lungu
here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
He said any initiative to improve the agriculture sector in the
country should take into account the welfare of professional staff
because they are the forerunners of the implementation process.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture, as a key sector in the development of the country,
should have a well motivated workforce because technical and
professional advice is cardinal for the planning, organization and
implementation of any program, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to Lungu, one of the reasons for the poor performance
of the Agriculture Sub-sector Investment Program is lack of
consultation by the government and donors with the implementing
staff.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, farmers are already urging the union to embark on
road development in rural areas as the roads in disrepair have
been an hindrance to free crop marketing by small-scale farmers.
</P>
<P>
Most farmers had no option but to sell their crop at give-away
prices because of lack of access to market. 
