<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Makes Flying Start in Asian U-19 Youth Football Group-4 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh booters gave a good
account of themselves to make a flying start in the 32nd Asian
Youth (Under-19) Football Championship Group-4 by swamping the
Maldives 4-1 in Friday's second match played in Rajshahi, a
northwestern city of Bangladesh,the Independent newspaper reported
here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh took the advantage of home ground and crowd went for
a full action immediately after kick-off and kept up the momentum
with wild cheering from a jam-packed stadium.
</P>
<P>
In Friday's inaugural match, Asian giant Iraq crushed Nepal by
seven goals, showing their formidable strength and excellent skill.
</P>
<P>
Iraq will face Maldives at 4 p.m. and Bangladesh will meet
Nepal at 6 p.m. in the two matches to be held on July 9. 
</P>
