<HEADLINE> Five Taiwan Fishermen Saved from Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 8 (Xinhua) -- A frontier police force in east
China's Fujian Province has saved five Taiwan fisherman after
their docked boat caught fire.
</P>
<P>
Fire broke out on the boat, which was anchored at a port in
Zhaoan county in the province, at about 10 p.m. on July 3.
</P>
<P>
The fire originated when sparks caused by a short circuit in a
cabin ignited styrofoam stored on the boat, the police said.
</P>
<P>
Thick smoke billowed from the cabin at the front part of the
boat, and tongues of fire threatened dozens of wooden boat nearby.
</P>
<P>
Frontier police in the city of Fuzhou rushed to the scene and
extinguished the fire after more than one hour.
</P>
<P>
They saved five fishermen on board, and the boat worth 2
million yuan (about 250,000 U.S. dollars) was not badly damaged.
</P>
</TEXT>
