<DOCNO> XIE20000708.0161 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> G-7 Finance Ministers Meeting Opens in Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Finance ministers from the Group of
Seven (G-7) most industrialized nations on Saturday opened their
meeting in Fukuoka, southwestern Japan, to discuss ways to
maximize the benefits of the information technology (IT)
revolution around the globe, the Kyodo news agency said.
</P>
<P>
The finance ministers are also expected to discuss issues
pertaining to debt-relief measures for heavily indebted poor
countries, ways to reform the International Monetary Fund, and
ways to crack down on tax evasion and money laundering.
</P>
<P>
The meeting of the finance chiefs from the G-7 -- Britain,
Canada, France, Germany, Italy, Japan and the United States, will
lay the groundwork for a summit of Group of Eight (G-8) nations in
Okinawa later this month.
</P>
<P>
At Saturday's talks, the finance ministers will for the first
time hold in-depth discussions on effects of the IT revolution on
macroeconomic, financial and tax policies.
</P>
<P>
They are poised to agree on the importance of setting
internationally coordinated rules and regulations in these spheres,
Kyodo quoted G-7 sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The G-7 ministers are also likely to agree that national
regulatory and supervisory authorities should cooperate in
overseeing e-commerce,they said.
</P>
<P>
Taxing e-commerce is another major topic for discussion. The
ministers are expected to discuss problems arising from patenting
new ways of doing business, such as e-commerce marketing.
</P>
<P>
IT-related issues will also figure prominently at the G-8
summit to be held on the southernmost island of Okinawa July 21-23.
The G-8 is the G-7 plus Russia.
</P>
<P>
As for IMF reform, the G-7 ministers are to adopt a package of
proposals that will strengthen the Washington-based IMF's crisis-
prevention functions and discourage long-term repeat borrowing, an
international financial source said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
