<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> (RECAST) Facts &AMP; Figures: Two-Way Trade With North America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Following are the latest facts and
figures about China's foreign trade with major North American
partners in the first five months of 2000, provided by the General
Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
-- Sino-U.S. trade: 27.239 billion U.S. dollars, up 24.9
percent. Exports to the U.S., 18.883 billion U.S. dollars, up 29.3
percent; Imports, 8.356 billion U.S. dollars, up 15.8 percent.
</P>
