<HEADLINE> Fiji's Military Reaches Agreement with Coup Group  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Fiji's 27 hostages will be
released on the same day that the Great Council of Chiefs is
convened, the Australian Radio Company ABC reported Saturday
morning.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached between the military authorities and
the coup group headed by George Speight in talks which stretched
into the early hours of Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
According to the solution, the chiefs will select a new
civilian president and at the same time end the military rule
which started on June 29.
</P>
<P>
The military president Frank Bainimarama has offered to step
down so the Great Council of Chiefs can appoint a new civilian
president.
</P>
<P>
The ethnic Indian former prime minister Mahendra Chaudhry along
with other around 40 officials were held hostage on June 6. Since
then the crisis is in fact focused on the distribution of power
between the indigenous power groups. 
</P>
