<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA -- An overloaded truck ran out of the road in Angola's
south central Huila province, killing 42 and injuring 34, the
Angolan official news agency Angop reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to a report issued by Angop without mentioning the
date, the accident occurred when a Volvo-brand truck ran out of
the road and overturned. (Angola-Accident)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Five people died Friday when the Cessna 310
airplane they were flying from The San Fernando airport to the
Martin Garcia island in Argentina fell to the ground.
</P>
<P>
Argentine Air Force sources said that the victims are the two-
man crew of the plane and three passengers who were flying to the
Martin Garcia island to teach classes. (Argentina-Plane Crash)
</P>
