</P>
<P>
MANAGUA -- Some 1,800 persons have been evacuated from their
houses in zones of high risk to refuges after the strong quake and
aftershocks that jolted Thursday Nicaragua, the authorities said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The tremor, which registered 5.4 degrees on the Richter scale,
killed four minors, injured 42 people, destroyed 140 houses and
partially damaged 894 more, said Army Major Norman Sanchez. (
Nicaragua-Quake)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA -- A palaeoanthropological site as old as some four
million years has been discovered at Galili locality in the Mulu
Basin, about 250 km east of Addis Ababa, the Ethiopian Information
and Culture Ministry announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
A research, which was conducted since 1998 by an Ethiopian
anthropologist Yohannes Haile-Selassie, unveiled the new site
which yielded a number of hominid and faunal remains, a press
release by the ministry said. (Ethiopia-Anthropology)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Nearly 50 years after a landmark paper proposed
the existence of what later came to be called jumping genes,
scientists are getting their first clear snapshot of one caught in
midair.
</P>
<P>
In Friday's issue of the journal Science, a University of
Wisconsin-Madison team describes the 3-dimensional, atomic
structure of an enzyme that allows a transposable genetic element
in a bacterium called Escherischia coli to "jump" from one part of
DNA to another. (US-Molecular-Gene)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia's Federation Council, the upper chamber of the
parliament, Friday repealed a bill, which entitles the head of
state to sack regional governors and chairmen of legislative if
they breach federal legislation.
</P>
<P>
The bill, aimed to amend the draft law on "the general
principles of organizing legislative (representative) and
executive branches of state power in Russia's territories", was
dismissed by a vote of 16 "for and 83 senators "against" with nine
abstentions. (Russia-Bill-Veto)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. Defense Department said that it is ready
to conduct the third test of a planned National Missile Defense (
NMD) system Friday night.
</P>
<P>
A four-hour launch window opens at 7:00 p.m. local time (0200
GMT Saturday) at Vandenberg Air Force Base in California State
where a target missile is poised for launch. (Missile-Test)
</P>
<P>
