<HEADLINE> College Entrance Exam Enters Second Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As students bent over their test papers for the national
college entrance examination yesterday, many anxious parents
waited outside schools under the scorching sun, according to China
Daily.
</P>
<P>
The scene will continue throughout the weekend. The Ministry of
Education sources said that over 3.88 million students throughout
China were taking the test this weekend, which is widely regarded
as the determiner of a student's future because China's colleges
evaluate applicants based on their test scores.
</P>
<P>
College and universities across the country will accept 2
million students this year, said Qu Zhenyuan, director of the
ministry's Department for College Students' Affairs.
</P>
<P>
To increase the enrollment, the ministry gave the entrance exam
twice this year in Beijing, Shanghai and Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
This examination system will be repeated in these three areas
and may be tried in other cities in later future, said Qu.
</P>
<P>
Nowadays in China, a growing number of parents have come to
regard higher education as a ticket to prosperity for their
children because of the fierce competition for jobs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
