<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Plant 72 Million Saplings During Monsoon Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government has set
a target of planting 72 million saplings under the country-wide
Monsoon Tree Plantation Campaign beginning August 10, according to
the Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
In this connection Federal Minister for Environment Omar Asghar
Khan chaired an Inter-Provincial Ministerial meeting to discuss
arrangements for the plantation drive here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized the need for improved forests management in the
country.
</P>
<P>
He called for involving community-based organizations, saying
that for expansion of forestry resource base, private sector,
especially farming community should be involved to undertake tree-
plantation on their lands during the monsoon season.
</P>
<P>
Asghar Khan emphasized that the government is concerned over
rapid deforestation and desertification taking place in the
country especially in the watershed areas.
</P>
<P>
He urged the provincial forest departments to mobilize and
motivate the masses and private sector through media and other
sources in order to get their support for successful launching of
plantation drive and post-planting care.
</P>
<P>
Monitoring and proper feedback on plantation drive are
imperative and key to success in achieving the tree planting
targets, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
