<HEADLINE> Pakistani ANF Recovers Large Quantity of Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 8 (Xinhua) -- An Anti-Narcotics Force team in
Pakistan's Balochistan province on a tip-off raided a place near
Gawadur port and recovered 1,400 kilograms of hashish Thursday
night, according to the Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The drug traffickers were trying to ship the drugs to the
Middle East through sea for which a launch was arranged. Due to
roughsea they could not get the launch in time.
</P>
<P>
A foreign national who came to Pakistan for arranging
transportation has been nominated and a case registered against
him. Search is underway to arrest him.
</P>
<P>
In other cases, Rawalpindi police arrested 10 accused from
various areas, recovering 184 grams of haras (cannabis resin), 46
grams of heroin and some illegal arms. 
