<HEADLINE> Canada to Seek Trade Interests in South America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Canadian International Trade
Minister Pierre Pettigrew will visit Chile, Argentina, Uruguay and
Colombia between July 9 and August 2 to advance Canadian business
interests in South America.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released here Friday, Pettigrew said what he
will discuss with the South American countries are such issues as
the status of the Free Trade Area of the Americas negotiations.
</P>
<P>
