strategic move," he said, adding that the region holds tremendous
opportunities for Canadian businesses.
</P>
<P>
According to Canada's official statistics, two-way trade
between Canada and Chile totaled 782 million Canadian dollars (
about 526 million U.S. dollars) in 1999, an 11.8 percent increase
from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Canada's two-way trade with Colombia reached 535.6 million
Canadian dollars (about 360 million U.S. dollars) in 1999. Its two-
way trade with Argentina and Uruguay amounted respectively to 515
million (about 347 million U.S. dollars) and to 126.7 million (
about 85 million U.S. dollars) in the same year. 
