<HEADLINE> Lewis Named 'Champ of the Year' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Britain's world heavyweight champion
Lennox Lewis will receive another prestigious boxing honor after
his title defence against Francois Botha at the London Arena next
week.
</P>
<P>
Lewis, generally regarded as the true world champion, will be
presented with the World Boxing Council's Champion of the Year
award from WBC president Jose Sulaiman at the post-fight press
conference.
</P>
<P>
"The WBC has voted Lennox as the Champion of the Year 1999. He
is a wonderful example to young people, great for the WBC and for
world boxing," said Sulaiman.
</P>
<P>
The South African-born Botha goes into the 15 July contest as a
rank outsider.
</P>
<P>
But Botha, who is now a US citizen, will not go home empty-
handed even if he loses to Lewis, as he will be presented with a
commemorative medal after the bout.
</P>
<P>
The new chairman of the Board of Control, Lord Brooks of
Tremorfa, will also receive a plaque from the WBC to mark his
election to the senior post in British boxing. 
</P>
