<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: Foreign Trade of Special Economic Zones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Following are the latest facts and
figures about foreign trade of China's Special Economic Zones (
SEZs) in the first five months of this year, released by the
General Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
Trade turnover: 19.949 billion U.S. dollars, up 34.3 percent;
Exports: 10.168 billion U.S. dollars, up 37.5 percent; Imports: 9.
780 billion U.S. dollars up 31.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Trade turnover of Economic and Technological Development Zones
and Special Open Areas: 16.167 billion U.S. dollars, up 52.7
percent. Exports, 7.078 billion U.S. dollars, up 46.2 percent;
Imports, 9.089 billion U.S. dollars, up 58.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Trade turnover of High-Tech Industrial Development Zones: 5.656
billion U.S. dollars, up 61.7 percent. Exports, 2.634 billion U.S.
dollars up 56.3 percent; Imports, 3.022 billion U.S. dollars, up
66.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Trade turnover of China's Bonded Areas: 5.599 billion U.S.
dollars, up 55.1 percent. Exports, 1.803 billion U.S. dollars, up
24.3 percent; Imports, 3.796 billion U.S. dollars, up 75.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Trade turnover of China's 14 coastal open cities: 50.396
billion U.S. dollars, up 39.4 percent. Exports, 26.709 billion U.S.
dollars up 34.6 percent; Imports, 23.687 billion U.S. dollars, up
45.2 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
