<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: China's Foreign Trade by Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 8 (Xinhua) -- Following are the latest statistics
of China's foreign trade from January to May 2000, provided by the
General Administration of Customs:
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume in January topped 32.043 billion U.S.
dollars, up 50.7 percent from the same period of 1999. Exports in
the month grew 47.6 percent to 16.784 billion U.S. dollars, and
imports rose 54.2 percent to 15.259 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- February saw an increase of 43.1 percent from the same
month of 1999, to 28.192 billion U.S. dollars, with exports at 14.
764 billion dollars, up 34.4 percent, and imports at 13.428
billion dollars, up 54.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
-- The foreign trade volume in March hit 37.942 billion U.S.
dollars, up 30.0 percent. Exports surged 35.9 percent to 20.131
billion U.S. dollars, and imports rose 24.0 percent to 17.811
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume in April reached 38.861 billion U.S.
dollars, up 35.8 percent. Exports grew 38.7 percent to 20.500
billion U.S. dollars, and imports went up 32.8 percent to 18.361
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- The total trade volume in May hit 37.072 billion U.S.
dollars, up 27.1 percent. Exports grew 29.6 percent to 20.105
billion U.S. dollars, and imports reached 16.966 billion U.S.
dollars, up 24.3 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
