<HEADLINE> Cuba, US Olympic Committees Sign Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, July 8 (Xinhua) -- The Cuban and United States Olympic
Committees signed Saturday an agreement of sports cooperation ,
the first of its kind between the two nations in more than 40
years.
</P>
<P>
The document was signed by Cuban Olympic Committee president
Jose Ramon Fernandez and his U.S. counterpart William J. Hybi,
during a ceremony in Havana.
</P>
<P>
The agreement foresees cooperation in the Olympic sports, the
combat to the use of forbidden substances, and maintenance of
communication between the two Olympic committees, said Fernandez.
</P>
<P>
"We are very satisfied with the (Hybi) visit, during which an
stage has been completed, as we had foreseen it in conversations
previously held," said the Cuban sports official.
</P>
<P>
Hybi said that "it is a pleasure for the U.S Olympic Committee
to close a deal of collaboration with its counterpart of the
island, and we expect that a wider collaboration between the two
countries will also occur."
</P>
<P>
This is a great opportunity to have a good start in the
cooperation between the Olympic committees of the United States
and Cuba, to have some kind of collaboration between our athletes,
" said Hybi.
</P>
<P>
Hybi said of eventual desertions of Cuban sportsmen in
competitions in the United States, that there will be difficulties,
"now and in the future, and we will work for a joint solution" to
this problem.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. sports official said that Cuba and United States are
very competitive in the Pan-American Olympic games, as it was
shown in the continental contest of Winnipeg in 1999.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
