<HEADLINE> Peru Rejects U.S. Pressures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
De Trazegnies said about the possibility of sanctions applied
to Peru by the United States if his country does not abide by the
proposals of the Organization of American States (OAS) for
democratic reforms, that his government committed itself to
examine an agenda, not to implement recommendations.
</P>
<P>
U.S. State Department spokesman Richard Boucher said that his
country pressures President Alberto Fujimori to implement the OAS
recommendations.
</P>
<P>
"Everybody has a right to speak about whatever he or she wants,
but in reality, I do not think that friends must look to each
other in the eyes with a stick in their hand," he said.
</P>
<P>
An OAS high-level mission led by its general secretary Cesar
Gaviria and Canadian Foreign Minister Lloyd Axworthy visited
recently Peru and handed Fujimori proposals for the improvement of
democratic institutions in the country.
</P>
<P>
De Trazegnies said that any warning from the United States has
to be unilaterally taken by the Fujimori government.  
</P>
