<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peru Suspends Poultry Imports from Honduras </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Peru's Agrarian Health National
Service (SENASA) suspended Saturday the import of several poultry
products, byproducts and eggs from Honduras, because of the recent
outbreak of the "Newcastle Velogenic" disease in that Central
American country.
</P>
<P>
The agency in charge of supervising the import of agriculture
and livestock products said that the imports suspension includes
fertile eggs for breeding and for consuming, chicks, chicken meat,
fighting cocks and wild or nursery-raised singing birds.
</P>
<P>
SENASA announced six cases of the "Newcastle Velogenic" disease
in the Honduran departments of Francisco Morazan and Cortes.
</P>
<P>
The institution also explained that the virus that causes the
disease is not endemic in Peru and for that reason those birds or
their products are not appropriate to be sold in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
